</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
The larva of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus martinus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinus">Epeorus martinus</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by the following characteristics: pairs of moderately long acute submedian spines on the abdominal terga 1-9, large but narrow gill 1 forming a sucking disc and gill 7 being unfolded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="66" type="habitat and biology">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Habitat and biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus martinus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinus">Epeorus martinus</taxonomicName>
larvae are found in mountain streams with a moderate current, at an elevation of 300-2800 m (
<bibRefCitation author="Nguyen, VV" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology" pageId="27" pageNumber="88" pagination="19 - 28" title="Larvae of the heptageniid mayfly genus Epeorus (Ephemeroptera: Heptageniidae) from Vietnam." volume="7" year="2004 a">Nguyen and Bae 2004a</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="66" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="66">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="66">
<bibRefCitation author="Webb, JM" journalOrPublisher="Canadian Journal of Arthropod Identification" pageId="28" pageNumber="89" pagination="1 - 55" title="Heptageniidae of the world. Part II. Key to the genera." volume="7" year="2008">Webb and McCafferty (2008)</bibRefCitation>
did not recognize the subgenera of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epeorus</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<taxonomicName authority="Chernova, 1981" authorityName="Chernova" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Belovius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Belovius" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Belovius</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Eaton, 1883" authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Iron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iron" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Iron</taxonomicName>
). However, we hold on the validity of subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Chernova, 1981" authorityName="Chernova" authorityYear="1981" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Belovius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Belovius" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Belovius</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Eaton, 1883" authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Iron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iron" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Iron</taxonomicName>
within genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Epeorus</taxonomicName>
(Boonsoong &amp; Braasch, 2010). Therefore, we propose 
<taxonomicName authority="Eaton, 1883" authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1883" class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Iron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Iron martinus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinus">Iron martinus</taxonomicName>
Braasch &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Soldán">Soldan</normalizedToken>
, 1984 = 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Heptageniidae" genus="Epeorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeorus (Iron) martinus" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinus" subGenus="Iron">Epeorus (Iron) martinus</taxonomicName>
Braasch &amp; 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Soldán">Soldan</normalizedToken>
, 1984
</paragraph>
